\pard\plain \ \f4\fs20\lang2057 {\fs28  (}{\b\fs28 b}{\fs28 ) Subsp. }{\b\fs28 litoralis}{\fs28  (Fries) Nyman,}{\i\fs28  Consp.}{\fs28  551 (1881) (}{\i\fs28 O. litoralis}{\fs28  Fries): stem 10-35 cm, usually simple, rarely with 1-2 pairs of short, suberect branches immediately below the inflorescence; lower internodes longer than the leaves. Leaves crenate to serrate, widest at or near the base. Bracts 8-20 mm. Early-flowering. 2n = 20.}{\i\fs28  Meadows by the sea. \bullet  Baltic region, extending to S. Norway and the Netherlands}{\fs28 .
