\pard \ {\fs28    }{\b\fs28 1. B. alpina}{\fs28  L.,}{\i\fs28  Sp. Pl}{\fs28 . 602 (1753). Glandular-hairy; stems 8-30(-40) cm, erect or ascending, simple. Leaves 10-25 \'d7 6-15 mm, ovate, obtuse to subacute, crenate-serrate. Bracts like the leaves but decreasing in size upwards, dull purple, exceeding the calyx. Calyx 6-8 mm; teeth as long as tube or shorter, narrowly triangular, obtuse. Corolla 15-20 mm, dull, dark purple. Capsule distinctly longer than calyx. 2n = 12, 24, 36.}{\i\fs28  Damp places; usually on base-rich soils. N. Europe, and southwards in the mountains to the Pyrenees, S Alps and S.W. Bulgaria.}{\fs28  ?Al Au Br Bu Cz Fa Fe Ga Ge He Hs Is It Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, W) Su.
