\pard \ {\fs28    }{\b\fs28 1. P. viscosa}{\fs28  (L.) Caruel in Parl.,}{\i\fs28  Fl. Ital.}{\b\fs28  6}{\fs28 : 482 (1885) (}{\i\fs28 Bartsia viscosa}{\fs28  L.). Glandular-hairy; stem 10-50(-70) cm, erect, usually simple. Leaves 10-45 \'d7 3-15 mm, oblong to lanceolate, acute to subacute, coarsely serrate. Bracts like the leaves, but decreasing in size upwards. Calyx 10-16 mm; teeth linear-lanceolate, nearly as long as tube. Corolla 16-24 mm, yellow (less often white), caducous. Capsule 7-9 mm, oblong, pubescent. Seeds c. 0\'b75 mm. 2n = 48.}{\i\fs28  Damp, grassy or sandy places. S. & W. Europe, northwards to S.W. Scotland; naturalized or casual further north.}{\fs28  Al Az Bl Br Co Cr Ga Gr Hb Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu [Be Da Ho].
